n%20in%20the%20railroad%20business%20for%2025%20years%2C%20mostly%20in%20middle%20management%20roles.%20It%20was%20his%20dream%20job%20and%20all%20he%20ever%20wanted%20to%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20when%20the%20world%20shut%20down%20in%202020%2C%20and%20he%20got%20laid%20off%2C%20he%20needed%20to%20figure%20something%20else%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20came%20to%20me%20one%20day%20like%20a%20clap%20of%20thunder%2C%26quot%3B%20Hatler%2C%20who%20is%20based%20in%20Pennsylvania%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHalter%20and%20his%20brother%20had%20long%20talked%20about%20the%20possibility%20of%20using%20rail%20to%20help%20alleviate%20the%20water%20crisis%20in%20the%20Navajo%20Nation.%20His%20brother%2C%20Chris%20Halter%2C%20runs%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.stbonaventuremission.org%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESt.%20Bonaventure%20Indian%20Mission%20and%20School%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20located%20on%20the%20southeastern%20edge%20of%20the%20reservation%2C%20which%20spans%20more%20than%2027%2C000%20square%20miles%20across%20parts%20of%20Arizona%2C%20New%20Mexico%2C%20and%20Utah.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENearly%20a%20third%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnndwr.navajo-nsn.gov%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ENavajo%20Nation%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20residents%20do%20not%20have%20access%20to%20reliable%2C%20clean%20drinking%20water%2C%20according%20to%20the%20tribe.%20The%20estimated%20population%20was%20over%20165%2C000%20in%202020%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdata.census.gov%2Fprofile%2FNavajo_Nation_Reservation_and_Off-Reservation_Trust_Land%2C_AZ--NM--UT%3Fg%3D2500000US2430%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecensus%20data%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20mission%20was%20already%20delivering%20water%20via%20trucks%20to%20250%20families%2C%20a%20small%20portion%20of%20the%20Navajo%20who%20are%20water-scarce.%20The%20families%20receive%20about%2040%20gallons%20of%20water%20a%20day%2C%20far%20less%20than%20the%20300%20gallons%20the%20average%20American%20family%20uses.%20The%20mission%20has%20relied%20on%20a%20local%20well%20to%20get%20the%20water%2C%20but%20if%20something%20happened%20to%20it%2C%20all%20those%20families%20would%20be%20without%20any%20water%20virtually%20overnight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20be%20honest%2C%20it%20was%20always%20the%20thing%20that%20would%20wake%20me%20up%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20night%2C%26quot%3B%20Chris%20Halter%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BIf%20that%20well%20shuts%20down%20for%20some%20reason%2C%20what%20would%20I%20do%20next%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20Halter's%20company%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjacobswell8.godaddysites.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJacob's%20Well%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20partnership%20with%20the%20mission%2C%20delivers%20thousands%20of%20gallons%20of%20water%20each%20month%20from%20Mississippi%20to%20the%20Navajo%20Nation%20via%20the%20BNSF%20Railway.%20The%20water-by-rail%20served%20as%20a%20lifeline%20in%202022%20when%20the%20well%20had%20to%20undergo%20repairs%20that%20lasted%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20operation%20has%20grown%20quickly%2C%20and%20Halter%20is%20focused%20on%20expanding%2C%20both%20to%20provide%20more%20water%20to%20the%20Navajo%20Nation%20but%20also%20potentially%20to%20other%20places%20in%20the%20West%2C%20where%20dried%20up%20rivers%20and%20reservoirs%20are%20leaving%20communities%20increasingly%20desperate%20for%20solutions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223209%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Tank%20car%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F664ea4e120abc1efe8fcc1b0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222049%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJacob's%20Well%20tank%20cars%20can%20carry%2021%2C000%20gallons%20of%20water.%3Cp%3EAndrew%20Halter%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a684fd17-93b4-488f-a009-a0f311e3306b%5C%22%3ESome%20thought%20the%20water-by-rail%20idea%20was%20crazy%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Halter%20first%20started%20calling%20railroads%20about%20transporting%20drinkable%20water%2C%20some%20thought%20the%20idea%20was%20crazy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20finally%20got%20in%20touch%20with%20Eunice%20Sun%20at%20BNSF%2C%20who%20currently%20serves%20as%20the%20business%20development%20manager%20of%20emerging%20markets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20haven't%20moved%20potable%20water%20prior%20to%20this%20opportunity%2C%20really%2C%20because%20the%20economics%20don't%20necessarily%20pencil%20out%20in%20order%20to%20pay%20for%20that%20water%20and%20pay%20for%20the%20transport%2C%26quot%3B%20Sun%20told%20BI.%20But%20when%20Halter%20came%20to%20her%2C%20she%20said%20he%20did%20a%20great%20job%20communicating%20his%20vision%20and%20business%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHalter%20said%20right%20now%20they%20can%20transport%20water%2C%20depending%20on%20fuel%20prices%20and%20other%20fluctuating%20costs%2C%20for%20around%2038%20cents%20a%20gallon.%20Currently%2C%20those%20costs%20are%20covered%20almost%20entirely%20by%20private%20donations%20to%20the%20mission.%20However%2C%20as%20the%20operation%20scales%20up%20and%20he%20transports%20more%20tank%20cars%20of%20water%2C%20those%20costs%20could%20come%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGetting%20a%20public%20utility%20to%20sell%20him%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20gallons%20of%20water%20per%20month%20was%20another%20story.%20%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20times%2C%20they%20think%20you're%20crazy%2C%26quot%3B%20Halter%20said.%20Still%2C%20they%20were%20able%20to%20work%20out%20a%20deal%20with%20the%20water%20department%20of%20Helena%2C%20Mississippi%2C%20where%20Jacob's%20Well%20collects%20its%20water%20before%20it%20travels%201%2C200%20miles%20by%20rail%20to%20the%20southwest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20it%20arrives%2C%20the%20Navajo%20families%20can%20pick%20up%20water%20from%20the%20mission%20or%20have%20it%20delivered%20to%20their%20homes%2C%20just%20as%20the%20well%20water%20is.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOriginally%2C%20Halter%20said%20he%20couldn't%20even%20find%20information%20about%20how%20the%20water%20would%20travel%2C%20and%20it%20took%20a%20lot%20of%20testing%20before%20and%20after%20transport%20to%20ensure%20the%20supply%20stayed%20safe%20to%20drink.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20kind%20of%20had%20to%20wing%20it%20and%20make%20up%20our%20own%20rules%20as%20we%20go%20along%20and%20figure%20some%20things%20out%20the%20hard%20way%2C%20which%20we%20did%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20took%20around%20eight%20months%20from%20when%20Halter%20first%20contacted%20BNSF%20for%20the%20first%20shipment%20to%20go%20out%2C%20and%20the%20operation%20has%20only%20grown%20since.%20Halter%20said%20they%20currently%20average%20around%20two%20tank%20cars%20a%20month%2C%20which%20each%20hold%2021%2C000%20gallons%20of%20water%2C%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Ebut%20the%20operation%20is%20capable%20of%20delivering%20200%2C000%20gallons%20a%20month%20if%20needed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20sent%20half%20a%20million%20gallons%20of%20water%20total%20in%202023.%20He's%20hoping%20to%20reach%202%20million%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Water%20truck%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F664ea52320abc1efe8fcc1b7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22400%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESt.%20Bonaventure%20Indian%20Mission%20and%20School%20provides%20more%20than%20250%20Navajo%20Nation%20families%20with%20water.%3Cp%3EAndrew%20Halter%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b3ba473f-e5dc-4635-868b-ff5aed905355%5C%22%3EEmergency%20water%20supply%20and%20the%20water%20crisis%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20unclear%20at%20this%20point%20how%20scalable%20or%20economically%20feasible%20water-by-rail%20will%20be%20in%20other%20places%2C%20but%20those%20involved%20are%20hopeful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChris%20Halter%20said%20he's%20currently%20conducting%20a%20study%20that%20he%20hopes%20will%20show%20the%20project%20has%20had%20a%20sound%20return%20on%20investment%20so%20that%20he%20can%20show%20tribal%2C%20local%2C%20and%20state%20governments%20that%20his%20is%20a%20feasible%20option.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESun%20said%20expanding%20Jacob's%20Well%20wouldn't%20come%20without%20growing%20pains%2C%20but%20that%20BNSF%20is%20happy%20to%20help%20support%20the%20project's%20growth.%20%26quot%3BIt%20tugs%20at%20your%20heartstrings%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20it's%20not%20often%20she%20gets%20to%20work%20on%20a%20project%20that%20has%20such%20a%20direct%20positive%20impact%20on%20a%20local%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHalter%20sees%20water-by-rail%20as%20something%20that%20could%20fill%20a%20serious%20need%20in%20all%20sorts%20of%20situations%2C%20from%20communities%20whose%20wells%20run%20dry%20to%20natural%20disasters.%20He's%20already%20been%20in%20touch%20with%20the%20state%20of%20New%20Mexico%20and%20FEMA.%20He's%20hopeful%20that%20rail%20will%20be%20among%20the%20solutions%20that%20help%20alleviate%20the%20broader%20water%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20getting%20a%20severe%20case%20of%20COVID-19%2C%20Halter%20lost%20the%20use%20of%20his%20right%20hand%20and%20was%20not%20able%20to%20go%20back%20to%20work%20on%20the%20railroad%2C%20so%20he%20now%20runs%20Jacob's%20Well%20full%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20become%20a%20driving%20mission%20to%20give%20these%20people%20water%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20want%20to%20be%20able%20to%20provide%20people%20with%20water%20at%20the%20lowest%20cost%20possible%2C%20and%20I%20want%20it%20to%20make%20enough%20money%20to%20support%20itself%2C%20but%20I%20don't%20need%20to%20get%20wealthy%20on%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20now%20the%20operation%20is%20run%20on%20donations%2C%20but%20they're%20hoping%20they%20can%20get%20grant%20money%20or%20other%20public%20funds%20to%20help%20support%20it%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWater%20is%20a%20human%20right%2C%26quot%3B%20Halter%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20they%20should%20be%20able%20to%20have%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20a%20news%20tip%20or%20a%20story%20to%20share%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Akvlamis%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Ekvlamis%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frailroad-worker-delivers-water-by-rail-navajo-nation-water-crisis-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1716892022000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F664ea5ee9fc063e829b4009c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frailroad-worker-delivers-water-by-rail-navajo-nation-water-crisis-2024-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Andrew%20Halter%20delivers%20water%20from%20Mississippi%201%2C200%20miles%20via%20the%20railroad%20to%20families%20on%20the%20Navajo%20Nation%20with%20the%20help%20of%20his%20brother.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kvlamis%40insider.com%20(Kelsey%20Vlamis)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frailroad-worker-delivers-water-by-rail-navajo-nation-water-crisis-2024-5%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BCan%20Do%20Anything%20To%20Save%20Party%26quot%3B%3A%20Tejashwi%20Yadav's%20Jibe%20At%20Nitish%20Kumar%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ERashtriya%20Janata%20Dal%20chief%20and%20Bihar's%20former%20Deputy%20Chief%20Minster%20Tejashwi%20Yadav%20took%20a%20dig%20at%20his%20erstwhile%20boss%20Nitish%20Kumar%20today%2C%20hinting%20that%20the%20Chief%20Minister%20could%20be%20ready%20for%20another%20switch%20after%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20election%20results%20are%20declared%20on%20June%204.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAfter%20June%204%2C%20our%20uncle%20can%20do%20anything%20to%20save%20